text: Dăbâca (; ) is a commune in Cluj County, Transylvania, Romania. It is composed of three villages: Dăbâca, Luna de Jos (Kendilóna) and Pâglișa (Poklostelke). == Demographics == According to the census from 2002 there was a total population of 1,804 people living in this commune. Of this population, 87.91% are ethnic Romanians, 7.53% are ethnic Hungarians and 4.43% ethnic Romani. == References == Category:Communes in Cluj County Category:Localities in Transylvania
